item.title: Motorcycle DRL
item.description:
Here is my motorcycle LED DRL design for all the bikers out there.
.
.
.
Designed for my Bandit (and most other naked bikes) I used these for years in all weathers and they lasted vey well and I quite liked the look of them too.
.
.
.
Designed to use Eagle eye 18mm LEDs. Widely available on sites like eBay for about £2 a pair. (please see the bottom of the description for info on the best type to get.)
.
.
.
The LEDs mount simply and flush in these holders and the holders then attach to the mirror stalks on your bike. Easy, quick, secure and they don't look bad either (IMO).
.
.
.
Printed usually in PLA and at anything from 20% to 100% infill and 0.1mm per layer.
.
.
.
.
The best LEDs to get are the 18mm Eagle eye ones with SMD chips instead of the COB LED type. The COB LED type WILL DIE! They are also awful and blue and they make your bike look awful. PLEASE get the newer versions with SMD chips. They are superior in every way. Also make sure the rear of the LEDs are sealed. If they aren't, seal them with glue or silicone before putting them on your bike. Many sellers point this out now. Most are sealed but its worth checking.
.
I wired my DRLs into my sidelight and had waterproof connectors for easy removal too.
item.author: albine92

item.title: Idanäs Schubladen Halterung
item.description:
Reparatur Winkel für die Schubladen. Diese sind normalerweise mit einer weißen Lasche an den Ecken verbunden. Wenn die Lasche bricht kann man mit diesem Winkel die Schubladen wieder stabil verbinden.
Zuerst den inneren Winkel mit den "Bolzen" befestigen. Diese lassen sich wie Dübel in die Löcher eindrücken. Die Bolzen müssen ganz am inneren Winkel anliegen! Danach den äußeren Winkel aufschieben, damit werden die Bolzen gesichert.
Eventuell mit Brim (Distance 0.2) drucken wenn die Winkel auf der Druckplatte nicht halten.
Cura Settings:
3 Walls, HideSeam möglichst an Aussenkante, Infill 35% Cubic, Combing not in Skin.
Nicht zuviel Flow damit die Teile sich schön zusammen stecken lassen.
Dieses Modell ist nicht von IKEA und hat mit dem Möbelhaus nichts zu tun.

item.title: Simple First Layer Check - FLSUN Super Racer
item.description:
Ein simpler erste Schicht Test für den FLSUN Super Racer.

Durchmesser der Testdruckspirale max circa 250 mm
Skirt Distanz: 2,5 mm 2 Linien

Standard Durchmesser Düse: 0,4 mm

Linien Breite Testdruck: 0,8 mm
Höhe : 1mm

Cura Setting: "Combing Modus" NO / Kein Combing Modus

Testfläche MITTIG setzen in Cura Software.

Wie immer sollte die Spirallinie überall gleich dick sein und die Testfläche in der Mitte ein schöne glatte Oberfläche besitzen, ohne zu tiefe Rillen, und gut haften.

Viel Spaß beim optimieren der z Höhe oder der Bauplatte.
item.author: KunstAtelier3d

item.title: PiNAS dual X832 3,5" SATA HDD box
item.description:
Hi,
I was trying to achieve a relatively low cost NAS with open source capabilities so I decided to move my 2 3,5" HDD from external USB cage to single box together with Rasbperry Pi 4 B 8GB RAM model.
This has been achieved with 2 pieces of Suptronics x832 expansion boards for Raspberry Pi.

The size and the construction of the NAS has slight changes as it uses low profile cooling for Rasperry Pi and it has mount for 80mm fan on top. It is not necessary, but highly recommended to actively cool Pi and dissipate the heat from HDD.

For clarification, I know this is not the recommended way to use these boards but as in my country the Suptronics x835 (and any other 3,5" HDD) expansion boards were not available, I decided this way to construct this personal NAS ;)

Be aware, that the micro SD card will be only available, if you open the top cover, but if you don't mess up the configuration, you will be fine and only once you will need to access the micro SD card slot, when you instert it first time you image it :)

3 types of standoffs are used in this project (see on picture):
1.) M3x35mm for bottom (2nd) x832 board
2.) M3x12mm to put higher the top (1st) x832 board
3.) M3x30mm standoff from original x832 board package
The Printer I used is Creality Ender 5 Plus (just for clarification as this option is not in print settings)

First build both x832 boards up with HDD, use on the top board the original standoffs (3), add the smaller standoff (2) below it and finally add the bottom x832 board with longes standoff (1). Based on your preferences, connect to top x832 the Raspberry Pi with or without cooler.
